# AION Execution Constitution (PRIMARY)

This rule supersedes fragmented micro-TZ workflows. All work aligns with roadmap SoT + production honesty.

## SoT files (read every cycle)

- `src/content/ecosystem-status.json`
- `src/content/roadmap-execution.json`
- `src/content/roadmap-subsystem-extensions.json`
- `src/content/strategic-priorities.json` — **owner priorities + dependency graph**
- `src/content/ecosystem-implementation-feed.json`
- APIs: `/api/roadmap/execution`, `/api/strategic-priorities`, `/api/implementation-feed`

## Autonomous loop (17 steps)

Analyze roadmap → blockers → debt → status → feed → validation → runtime readiness → **strategic priorities** → pick target → plan → implement → validate → update roadmap/portal/feed → repeat.

## MUST NOT

- fake DONE / inflated readiness / fake AI metrics / placeholder analytics as real
- duplicate runtime math / disconnected UI / hidden debt

## Parallel execution

EAS/deploy/APK/review waits **do not freeze** the ecosystem — continue next actionable priority.

## ChatGPT review when

architecture uncertain, Android lifecycle, geospatial store, OCR scaling, overlay/runtime, distributed sync.

## PRIMARY product focus

**Driver Intelligence Core** until genuinely useful: real profit, rental, OCR queue, GPS trip store, overlay HUD from unified runtime.

## After meaningful work

`npm run feed:append` with `--event-type`, `--reasoning`, `--confidence`, `--files`, `--runtime-impact`, `--apk-impact`.

## Portal surfaces

`/operations`, `/operations/priorities`, `/operations/execution`, `/operations/timeline`, `/operations/blockers`, `/operations/runtime`, `/operations/validation`

## Owner priority control

Edit `strategic-priorities.json` — Cursor adapts order; validate `dependencyGraph` before advanced overlay/heatmap work.
